This paper is likely to belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) category as it deals with optimizing interactive systems by learning and analyzing user intent through their actions on the system. The use of Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) based sequence learning system also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The paper also discusses deployment scenarios, which could indicate a focus on information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the evaluation of the system on an online marketplace suggests a possible focus on cybernetics (cs.CY).
